	<title>Datatypes</title>
 
	<para>When starting with a new model you are likely to start with modeling some entities to hold our business data. As type information in several places in the model
	 (for example the information that the countries name is a <literal>String</literal> is needed in the entity and the UI definition) central datatypes can be defined and 
	 referenced from the needed locations. The datatypes also have the benefit that you are able to provide additional information of the specific type (think of 
	 maximum length for a string or an upper bound for an integer).</para>

	<formalpara>
		<title>Sample datatype definition</title>

		<programlisting language="Java">
textdatatype CountryName {
	maxLength 32
}</programlisting>
	</formalpara>
	
	<para>
		The above examples defines a text datatype of the name <literal>CountryName</literal> and restricts the maximum length of the country 
		name to 32. The types and properties of the different dataypes are explained in the following section 	
	</para>
	
